---
title: Onion Crunch Chicken with Mashed Sweet Potatoes, Roasted Green Beans & Honey Dijon Dressing
description: Crispy chicken + honey mustard is a match made in mealtime heaven. And because we’re all about making sure your mealtimes are heavenly, we took that classic combo and chef’d it up a bit (still making sure it’s on your table in 30). To start, chicken breasts are brushed with honey mustard dressing, then coated with a mixture of Monterey Jack and crushed fried onions. The chicken’s roasted to juicy perfection and served with creamy mashed sweet potatoes and roasted green beans. There’s more honey mustard on the side for dunking and drizzling—because you deserve it.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/onion-crunch-chicken-7a330179.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6463f35e8ab1333a8ca24dd0.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/onion-crunch-chicken-6463f35e8ab1333a8ca24dd0
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 550 mg
---

Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces.

Using your hands, finely crush @crispy fried onions{1} in their bag. Transfer to a #small bowl{}; stir in @Monterey Jack cheese{¼%cup}.

Reserve @honey Dijon dressing{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a second small bowl (you'll use it in step 3).

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return sweet potatoes to pot. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread chicken out across entire sheet.)

Evenly spread tops of chicken with a thin layer of reserved dressing. Mound coated sides with onion crust, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Toss @green beans{6%oz} on empty side of same sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, add green beans to a second sheet; roast green beans on top rack and chicken on middle rack.)

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Check chicken periodically—if the crust browns too quickly, loosely cover with foil. Additionally, if green beans finish before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

Meanwhile, mash sweet potatoes with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt using a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide mashed sweet potatoes, green beans, and chicken between #plates{}. Serve with remaining dressing on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.